qa.question: Mark has a garden with flowers. He planted plants of three different colors in it. Ten of them are yellow, and there are 80% more of those in purple. There are only 25% as many green flowers as there are yellow and purple flowers. How many flowers does Mark have in his garden?

result.english_raw: Mark has a total of 45 flowers in his garden. 10 of them are yellow, 30 are purple, and 5 are green.
